ggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ahh1665702795148.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ahh1665702795148.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ahh1665702795148.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ahh1665702795148\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Design Layout Worksheet\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Design Layout Worksheet enables you to create the layout of the component, and bind individual elements to objects in the component structure.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__p_d5510e1_d5511e1_d5512e1\">For Dynamic and Static Server Pages components, Uniface inserts the basic HTML and references to JavaScript and styles required to generate a valid HTML page.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__p_d5513e1_d5514e1_d5515e1\">To complete the layout, you need to insert HTML elements that are bound to the component structure, and add your own page design elements to control the page appearance.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__section_ims_hj2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1167428e61\">Tools</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__ul_isp_3j2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__li_d2621e1_d2622e1_d2623e1\">Resource Browser—lists objects in the component\n               structure and code snippets that you can insert into the layout. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__li_d2624e1_d2625e1_d2626e1\">Layout Editor—HTML source editor for editing the\n               layout. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__section_bhw_3j2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1167428e76\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__ul_pkd_kj2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__li_d2627e1_d2628e1_d2629e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hxr1705401640523.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxr1705401640523.html\" title=\"When creating the layout, elements in the layout must be bound to the component data structure as defined in the Component Editor. You can do this by copying the Uniface objects from the component structure and inserting them as HTML in the layout.\">Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__ul_rkd_kj2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__li_d2630e1_d2631e1_d2632e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahh1665702795148__li_d2633e1_d2634e1_d2635e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owk1704697555747.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Layout</a><p>A layout defines the way data is arranged, formatted, and styled for presentation to the user, either on screen or in print.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zur1665702620176.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Binding Web Layout to Component Structure</a><p>Binding refers to the way in which layout elements are connected to data structures and triggers in the component structure. It ensures that data is displayed by the appropriate HTML elements in the web page, and that the correct trigger is executed when data in a field is changed.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525687\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525687\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Design Layout Worksheet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Design Layout Worksheet The Design Layout Worksheet enables you to create the layout of the component, and bind individual elements to objects in the component structure. For Dynamic and Static Server Pages components, Uniface inserts the basic HTML and references to JavaScript and styles required to generate a valid HTML page. To complete the layout, you need to insert HTML elements that are bound to the component structure, and add your own page design elements to control the page appearance. Tools Resource Browser—lists objects in the component structure and code snippets that you can insert into the layout. Layout Editor—HTML source editor for editing the layout. How to Insert Uniface Objects in the Server Page Layout Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Related Links Layout A layout defines the way data is arranged, formatted, and styled for presentation to the user, either on screen or in print. Binding Web Layout to Component Structure Binding refers to the way in which layout elements are connected to data structures and triggers in the component structure. It ensures that data is displayed by the appropriate HTML elements in the web page, and that the correct trigger is executed when data in a field is changed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}